<paragraph id="343472341719A93698CCFF0B7B81FE5E" blockId="40.[151,1436,151,418]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Male. Forewing irregularly light-spotted. Venation typical for the genus. Forewing crossveins m-cu and cu separate. Sc and 
<collectionCode id="529AEAF11719A936998FFF2379DBFEFE" box="[389,408,232,258]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">R</collectionCode>
separate. Cu2 and A separate. Hind wing Sc and 
<collectionCode id="529AEAF11719A9369BE7FF237C43FEFE" box="[1005,1024,232,258]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">R</collectionCode>
fusing before costa at crossvein s. Stem of M and Cu1 located distantly from each other. False vein of convolution running near and along stem of Cu1. Median cell open. Fork 1 present. Forewing length 8.0 mm, hind wing lenght 6.0 mm. Maxillary palp formula I-(
<collectionCode id="529AEAF11719A936991CFEAB791CFE86" box="[278,351,352,378]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">III-IV</collectionCode>
)-II-V. Vertex ochraceous, with 7 large ochraceous setal warts. Small setose wart on proepisternum present, with larger setose area on precoxale (preepisternum).
</paragraph>
<caption id="60F422BC1719A936989DF8C77AB8F8BA" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" startId="40.[151,269,1804,1828]" targetBox="[192,1369,469,1755]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="343472341719A936989DF8C77AB8F8BA" blockId="40.[151,1436,1804,1862]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="06FFAE261719A936989DF8C7791CF8D8" bold="true" box="[151,351,1804,1828]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">FIGURES 55–58.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F38B09B71719A936996DF8C67B76F8DF" authority="(Martynov, 1934)" authorityName="Oláh &amp; Johanson" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Oláh &amp; Johanson" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[359,821,1804,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydromanicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feminalis">
<emphasis id="06FFAE261719A936996DF8C67A2EF8D8" box="[359,621,1805,1828]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Hydromanicus feminalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="501A0FC51719A9369A76F8C77B6EF8DF" author="Martynov, A. B." box="[636,813,1804,1827]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="ref109396" refString="Martynov, A. B. (1934) Trichoptera Annulipalpia. Tableaux analytiques de la Faune de l'URSS. L'Institut Zoologique de l'Academie des Science 13, 343 pp." type="book" year="1934">Martynov, 1934</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, non-type, male. 55 — genitalia, lateral; 56 — genitalia, dorsal; 57 — phallus, lateral; 58 — phallus apex, ventral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="343472341719A93698CCF8BE7DDFF823" blockId="40.[151,1436,1909,2015]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Remarks: This is the only species in the genus having this latter, possibly primitive character, present. The species was described from South Ussuriland and Sutchan. Its occurrence in 
<collectingCountry id="4C9C32A41719A9369C2EF8567CC4F84B" box="[1060,1159,1949,1975]" name="Vietnam" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
was unexpected due to the long distance to the 
<typeStatus id="EB30CC961719A93699B3F80E79A8F823" box="[441,491,1989,2015]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
locality. However, all 
<specimenCount id="228DB9BD1719A9369AF4F80E7B19F823" box="[766,858,1989,2015]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="male">3 males</specimenCount>
collected in North 
<collectingCountry id="4C9C32A41719A9369C4FF80E7CEBF823" box="[1093,1192,1989,2015]" name="Vietnam" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
are almost identical
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="343472341718A937989DFF537BC7FF26" blockId="41.[151,1436,152,218]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">with the drawings by Martynov in the original description, as well as those by Ivanov (1997). Here we presented additional information on the morphology of the species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
